The paper discusses the use of machine learning in malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the interpretability of machine learning models, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the need for tuning and optimizing solutions, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of existing interpretability techniques in the malware analysis domain, which falls under the category of systems and information theory (cs.SI).
